Pages = {202-211},
Note = {1st International Conference on Smart Medical, IoT and Artificial
   Intelligence (ICSMAI), Saidia, MOROCCO, AUG 18-20, 2024},
Abstract = {One of the most prominent computer software platforms ever created is
   Web Browser (WB). They are a gateway to access to Internet and many
   electronic transactions such e-mail, e-commerce, e-learning among
   others. Attackers Of cybercrime are aware that WB like Google chrome,
   Apple Safari, Opera, along with Mozilla Firefox is installed on all
   devices such computers, smartphones, Watch, Smart-TVs, and even cars.
   This ubiquity attract theme to focus to this big opportunity to exploit
   their vulnerabilities, but modern browsers come with many inbuilt
   functionalities to combat these attacks. Unfortunately, attackers are
   conscious that the week pieces in WB landscape is user, that big percent
   off them are not aware about security and that they don't understand how
   to protect themselves, one of the vulnerabilities that attackers know
   well is that users are welling to quickly access to the content of
   internet by clicking in and accepting all options that can speed up
   their navigation desired material. by manipulating browser security
   setting to gain access to user's devices. In this paper, we provide our
   methodology for developing a ChatGPT Language Learning Model (LLM)
   example with an extension designed to assist users in understanding
   browser preferences risk using a chatbox interface. The chatbot's
   purpose is to improve users' online safety by offering individualized
   recommendations based on their risk preferences through ongoing learning
   and adaption.},
